{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-post-template-tsx","path":"/posts/docker-engine-with-nvidia-gpu-support/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"7564812d-205c-52fd-bd2a-62e8038b5298","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 800px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/390f459a8e04c0ba7c94aef3d5e3bc7c/4b190/nvidia-docker.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 60%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/390f459a8e04c0ba7c94aef3d5e3bc7c/8ac56/nvidia-docker.webp 240w,\n/static/390f459a8e04c0ba7c94aef3d5e3bc7c/d3be9/nvidia-docker.webp 480w,\n/static/390f459a8e04c0ba7c94aef3d5e3bc7c/d00b9/nvidia-docker.webp 800w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/390f459a8e04c0ba7c94aef3d5e3bc7c/09b79/nvidia-docker.jpg 240w,\n/static/390f459a8e04c0ba7c94aef3d5e3bc7c/7cc5e/nvidia-docker.jpg 480w,\n/static/390f459a8e04c0ba7c94aef3d5e3bc7c/4b190/nvidia-docker.jpg 800w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n            type=\"image/jpeg\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/390f459a8e04c0ba7c94aef3d5e3bc7c/4b190/nvidia-docker.jpg\"\n            alt=\"nvidia-docker\"\n            title=\"\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>By default, Docker containers do not have access to the GPU. However, you can enable GPU support in Docker by using theÂ <a href=\"https://github.com/NVIDIA/nvidia-docker\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">NVIDIA Docker</a>. This post is a step-by-step guide to enabling Nvidia GPU support in Docker Engine.</p>\n<h2 id=\"prerequisites-and-verification\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#prerequisites-and-verification\" aria-label=\"prerequisites and verification permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Prerequisites and Verification</h2>\n<p>Before you start, ensure you have installed the NVIDIA GPU drivers on your system. You can check the driver installation by running the following command:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">$ nvidia-smi</code></pre></div>\n<p>And you can also verify your docker engine installation by running:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">$ <span class=\"token function\">docker</span> run <span class=\"token parameter variable\">--gpus</span> all nvidia/cuda:10.1-runtime nvidia-smi</code></pre></div>\n<p>If the command returns the GPU information, the drivers/docker engine is installed correctly.</p>\n<h2 id=\"install-nvidia-container-toolkit\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#install-nvidia-container-toolkit\" aria-label=\"install nvidia container toolkit permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Install NVIDIA Container Toolkit</h2>\n<p>If GPU support is not enabled, you can continue with the following steps to install the NVIDIA Docker.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>root<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token comment\"># curl -s -L https://nvidia.github.io/nvidia-docker/gpgkey | apt-key add -</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>root<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token comment\"># DISTRIBUTION=$(. /etc/os-release;echo $ID$VERSION_ID)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>root<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token comment\"># curl -s -L https://nvidia.github.io/nvidia-docker/$DISTRIBUTION/nvidia-docker.list | tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/nvidia-docker.list</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>root<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token comment\"># apt update --fix-missing &amp;&amp; apt-get install -y nvidia-docker</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>root<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token comment\"># systemctl restart docker</span></code></pre></div>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/2019-11-25---Docker-Engine-with-Nvidia-GPU-Support//posts/docker-engine-with-nvidia-gpu-support","tagSlugs":["/tag/virtualization/","/tag/docker/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-11-25T23:20:00.000Z","description":"tips to enable Nvidia GPU support in Docker Engine.","tags":["Virtualization","Docker"],"title":"Docker Engine with Nvidia GPU Support","socialImage":{"publicURL":"/static/390f459a8e04c0ba7c94aef3d5e3bc7c/nvidia-docker.jpg"}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/2019-11-25---Docker-Engine-with-Nvidia-GPU-Support//posts/docker-engine-with-nvidia-gpu-support"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","288581551","401334301"],"slicesMap":{}}